      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NANGAR NUGGET (7) was well fancied last time on the back of some sparkling form, which included a four-start winning streak, but could only manage fifth (25.79) at Q Lakeside. Got the money at his only try from this box. Rates on top in this line up. LIAM BLUEY (8) broke a string of placings finishing in the money two on end before a last start fourth (28.02) at this track. Form at the trip sound including four wins. Comes through a solid form race last start. Has ability and a bold showing is expected. HE'S A BONUS (3) was prominent throughout when winning two back but could manage only midfield last time when 4th and beaten 7 lengths at Grafton (20.38). Should be in this for a long way. JAVEN'S SHOT (2) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.",
